posts.subject: Response to a horrified Canadian - concerning Colonel Stuart Scheller
posts.body:
I know something about this case. May not much more than knowing nothing at all. And I DO wish to give this colonel credit for his self reflection.


But the fact is - it was the military's job to carry out the orders of our President. Unfortunately, they pulled an Archie Bunker. "In America, when you are angry at the boss - you do a really shitty job".


Now, as a taxpayer, citizen, veteran. How am I supposed to receive this? Am I supposed to join sides with the "generals fuckup"? Condemn Biden for forcing them to do their job?


I do condemn Biden for not sacking his secretary of defense, and those who had any role in this massive fuckup. But why would I condemn Biden for righting a 20 yr mistake?


The ugly truth behind all of this is that those generals have been lying for 20 years - and none of them have lost anything for those lies. Only some unknown colonel.


Will tell you this, there are many in this country who will fight. Are aching to fight. And those generals should fear them very much.


The United States once fragged incompetent officers. Can happen again......


I spit on Biden, but I don't spit on him here.

posts.subject: They'll be fighting for their lives .....
posts.body:
First American citizen that is killed by a US soldier will set off such an orgy of killing - it will just be unbelievable to anyone who wasn't there.

No quarter, no mercy, nowhere to hide. 

Your military is not "part of us".  It just is another federal jobs program gone bad. So we have plenty of reason to hate you right now. Give us a citizen death and we'll act.

You won't have time to run or change your mind in the face of public ferocity. Most of you will throw down your arms and attempt to disappear.

ORGY.  That's what it will be you mindless cunt.

posts.subject: Open question - can anyone imagine a way to stabilize cryptocurrency?
posts.body:
Many of us have watched from the sidelines for years....lusting for a way to really displace government currency.  And this new connection between anonymous Monero and the I2P invisible internet overlay looks promising. 

Unfortunately, these wide swings in market value shatter such hopes. Real money must serve as a store of value.

I understand it is difficult for ANY currency to live up to this "store of value" requirement. It's still needed. Without a stable value - cryptocurrency will never achieve it's promise.

posts.body:
How in the hell did we manage to isolate the only Afghans who would not fight?

Taliban walked in, whispered "boo" - and 300,000 troops dropped their weapons.

It IS funny, but later on we do need to get serious about hunting down all the military clowns (both retired and active duty) so we can hang those who truly deserve it.

posts.subject: Another Socialist shithead who just does not get it .....
posts.body:
Most come out of college dumber than they went in. Even dumber, they perform this experiment on credit.

Unless you are picking up scarce skills. Like how to build computer chips or tiny nuclear power plants - universities are a waste of your time. It's like a summer school for retards who failed to do the work in high school, or couldn't afford to break out of the lowered educational standards of niggered schools.

So why flush this money (which this nation never really had) at all?

YOU would have been much better off if none of those funds had been spent....because even your grandkids will be paying for this mistake.

Here's a hint. I voted regularly and sent many letters to Congress begging for this spending to stop. None of it ever worked - not even a little bit. Congress is filled with welfare queens. They don't care.

While I haven't run this experiment, if I had overs would probably try simple assassination. And if enough people would just assassinate on a regular basis - we'd finally get Congressmen which listens - along with some competitive seats (courtesy of the random fill).

Writing Congress is like wasting your time supporting these unemployable professors and their overpaid bosses. It's destined to fail.

Just kill them. Be a force for change.

posts.subject: The autist

posts.body:
>>26002307-3415-4e9c-bc51-34badacf69ad
This is interesting and important to watch. I see the US government as trying same on it's citizens soon.

All this censoring was just a warmup so they can learn how to cut communications.

I wish independent people could fund more development of secure scuttlebutt (a mobile physical internet). I figure Tor will be cut. Less certain about I2P.  Every neighborhood should buy at least one Starlink receiver - then spread that connection via wifi/other RF transport).

Any communications system reliant on carriers is in the government's pocket.

>>ec383449-77d7-4f34-a39f-82f1148b89a3
Australia is an almost ideal case for establishing a great firewall. Oceans matter. So I suspect their government will soon cut access to Tor and other censorship evading technologies.

Accordingly I started listing the systems which might still work.

Delta chat - Voice over email  https://delta.chat/en/user-voices

Secure Scuttlebutt

Starlink

Embedded signalling within VOIP transmissions (always university papers but never hardware?)

I2P (had my doubts on this one - then found the link) https://www.opentech.fund/news/empirical-study-i2p-anonymity-network-and-its-censorship-resistance/

Deltachat may be the best bet. Deltachat via I2P might be wonderful.

>>d8d37faa-913f-49bc-938f-32cf01ba6fc0
It does appear that I2P works where other technologies won't.

>>26002307-3415-4e9c-bc51-34badacf69ad
They've shutdown all social media, all press, and are jamming the CB bands truckers use.

This is the future of the United States. All of this will be used on us.

It's time to start looking at I2P and Delta chat very seriously, and Deltachat users must have email accounts outside of Australia.
